    {
      "id": "b4bb41b7_92e1d5d9",
      "file_path": "ansible/roles/resource-data/tasks/main.yml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 28,
      "message": "I find it much more disturbing to have global variables. Coming from real programming languages it's quite painful in ansible to accept that madness.\nTo keep thing at least little bit sane for submodules called (in this case upload_resources.yml and that one further calls unarchive-resource.yml and then unarchive-{{ transport }}-resource.yml) it's good to keep \"passed parameters\" explicit. Ones saying that I broke that rule already in unarchive-resource.yml module where variables are not explicitly given to called \"unarchive-{{ transport }}-resource.yml\" but they are going as global vars. But it's mentioned in the comments.\n\nSo the reason is modularity as usually writing modules usable in many places, however called can always set that variable to some value. So no special reason. \nI would either keep explicit variables or relax it everywhere.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3957,
        "name": "Samuli Silvius",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "s.silvius@partner.samsung.com",
        "username": "silvius"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-20 16:56:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "876ebbc4_6b6156dd",
      "unresolved": true
    },
